  "body": "  [Problem E] Euler's theorem describes all matrices in with determinant as being rotation matrices. We can understand thus the operators given by such matrices in a geometric manner: rotate in a plane perpendicular to some pole vector (that is an eigenvector for the matrix), leaving the pole vector unchanged.  If with , can you describe geometrically (in a somewhat similar manner) the operators given by these matrices? How do these operators act on points in ?   "
